        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="lead">ToolKit — All‑in‑One File & Image Tools</p>
        <div class="meta">Last updated: November 18, 2025</div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="card">
      <p>This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>ToolKit</strong> ("we", "us", or "the app") handles information when you use the app or the online tools hosted at <a href="https://raja1068.github.io/Tools" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://raja1068.github.io/Tools</a>. By using ToolKit, you agree to the practices described in this policy.</p>

      <h2>1. Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
      <p>ToolKit is designed to respect user privacy. We do <strong>not</strong> collect, store, or share any personal information such as:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Names</li>
        <li>Email addresses</li>
        <li>Phone numbers</li>
        <li>Location data</li>
        <li>Device-specific identifiers</li>
        <li>Contact lists</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. File Processing and Temporary Handling</h2>
      <p>When you use ToolKit to process a file (for example converting a PDF, compressing an image, or removing an image background), the file is uploaded to the online service for the duration required to perform the requested operation. Files are processed and removed automatically. We do not keep or retain files after processing is complete.</p>

      <h2>3. Permissions</h2>
      <p>The Android app version of ToolKit requires the following permissions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>INTERNET</code> — to access the online tools and process files</li>
        <li><code>ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE</code> — to detect network connectivity</li>
      </ul>
      <p>ToolKit does <strong>not</strong> request permissions for storage, camera, contacts, microphone, or location by default. If you extend the app to add optional features that require additional permissions, those permissions will be requested explicitly and documented.</p>

      <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>The app loads and uses web-based tools hosted at the URL above. Those pages may rely on standard web platform features and may use third-party libraries to perform transformations. We aim to use secure connections (HTTPS) for all data transfers. If any third-party service used by the hosted tools collects information, that collection is governed by the third party’s own privacy policy.</p>

      <h2>5. No Account or Login</h2>
      <p>ToolKit does not require user registration, login, or the creation of accounts. All functionality is available without providing personal information.</p>

      <h2>6. Children’s Privacy</h2>
      <p>ToolKit is rated for general audiences (3+). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. If you believe a child has provided personal information to us, please contact us so we can take steps to remove the information.</p>

      <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
      <p>We use reasonable practices to protect files while in transit using HTTPS. However, no system can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. By using ToolKit, you acknowledge and accept that there are inherent risks when transferring files over the internet.</p>

      <h2>8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the <em>Last updated</em> date at the top of this page. Continued use of the app after changes indicates acceptance of the revised policy.</p>

      <h2>9. Contact</h2>
      <p>If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:</p>
      <p><a href="mailto:masoomtech.help@gmail.com">masoomtech.help@gmail.com</a></p>

